        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 4:22PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 422 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles north of La Verkin, or 14 miles west of Zion National Park.
This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Toquerville and Pintura.

This includes Interstate 15 between mile markers 27 and 34.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
